neutrons from the (p,n) reaction were detected
by the neutron polarimeter NPOl2.  The NPOl2 system
consists of six planes of two-dimensional
position-sensitive neutron detectors (1x1x0.1 m**3).
the first four detectors are made of liquid
scintillator bc519, and the last two detectors are made
of plastic scintillator bc408.  The position
resolutions are about 6 to 10 cm and about 4 to 8 cm
for liquid scintillators and plastic scintillators,
respectively, depending on positions.

the neutron time-of-flight facility at the
research center for nuclear physics (RCNP) was used for
the measurement.  One of four beam pulses was selected
to  yield an effective beam pulse separation of about
260 ns. Flight time was determined by using timing
signals  from the phototubes with an rf signal, and the
absolute timing calibration was performed using gamma
rays from the target.  Neutron kinetic energies were
determined from the flight time with fwhm resolution of
1.7 MeV.
